Privacy Policy for BMI Healthy Lifestyle
Last Updated: December 22, 2024

This Privacy Policy applies to the BMI Healthy Lifestyle app (hereafter referred to as "the Application"), created by OulouArk Studios (hereafter referred to as "Service Provider"). The Application is an ad-supported service and is intended for use "AS IS".

1. Information Collection and Use
The Application collects information when you download and use it. This information may include, but is not limited to:

Your device's Internet Protocol (IP) address.
The pages of the Application that you visit, including the time and date of your visit and the time spent on those pages.
The amount of time spent using the Application.
The operating system of your mobile device.
Please note that the Application does not gather precise location information of your mobile device.

The Service Provider may use the information provided to contact you from time to time regarding important updates, required notices, or marketing promotions.

For a better experience while using the Application, the Service Provider may require you to provide certain personally identifiable information, including but not limited to:

Email address: For account creation, authentication, and communication purposes.
Other optional details: If you choose to update your profile, this may include additional information such as display name, profile picture, or other details available through Firebase Authentication.
This information will be retained by the Service Provider and used in accordance with this privacy policy.

2. Third-Party Access
The Application uses third-party services to enhance the user experience. These services have their own privacy policies regarding the handling of data. The Application may share anonymized data with these third-party services to improve the app.

Some third-party services used by the Application include:

Google Play Services
AdMob (for advertisements)
You can review the privacy policies of these third-party services at the following links:

Google Play Services Privacy Policy
AdMob Privacy Policy
The Service Provider may disclose User Provided and Automatically Collected Information in the following cases:

As required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena, or similar legal process.
When the Service Provider believes in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect its rights, the safety of users or others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request.
With trusted service providers who work on the Service Provider's behalf and have agreed to adhere to the privacy policy's guidelines.
3. Opt-Out Rights
You can stop all collection of information by the Application by uninstalling it. You may use the standard uninstall process available on your mobile device or through the mobile application marketplace.

4. Data Retention Policy
The Service Provider will retain the data provided by users as long as you use the Application and for a reasonable period thereafter. If you wish to delete the data youâ€™ve provided via the Application, please contact the Service Provider at bmi.contact212@gmail.com, and your request will be processed in a timely manner.

5. Children's Privacy
The Application does not knowingly solicit or collect personal data from children under the age of 13. If it is discovered that a child under 13 has provided personal information, the Service Provider will immediately delete it from their servers. If you are a parent or guardian and you believe that your child has provided us with personal data, please contact us at bmi.contact212@gmail.com, and we will take necessary actions.

6. Security
The Service Provider is committed to safeguarding the confidentiality of your information. The Application implements physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to protect the information we process and maintain.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Any changes will be communicated by updating the date at the top of this Privacy Policy. Continued use of the Application constitutes your acceptance of any changes.

8. Your Consent
By using the Application, you consent to the processing of your information in accordance with this Privacy Policy, both in its current form and as amended in the future.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding your privacy while using the Application, or if you need clarification on the privacy practices, please contact us via email at: bmi.contact212@gmail.com.
